00:55.724 --> 00:58.158
<i>[Girl]</i>
<i>Cinderella flew through the air...</i>

00:58.226 --> 01:01.593
<i>far from all things</i>
<i>ugly and ordinary.</i>

01:01.663 --> 01:04.291
<i>When she landed at the ball,</i>
<i>she found herself...</i>

01:04.366 --> 01:07.698
<i>most impertinently surrounded</i>
<i>by pirates.</i>

01:07.768 --> 01:12.398
<i>There was Alf Mason,</i>
<i>so ugly his mother sold him</i>
<i>for a bottle of muscat.</i>

01:12.473 --> 01:17.000
<i>Bill Jukes,</i>
<i>every inch of him tattooed.</i>

01:17.077 --> 01:19.443
<i>And worst of them all,</i>

01:19.512 --> 01:23.812
Hook, with eyes blue
as forget-me-nots,

01:23.883 --> 01:28.444
save when he clawed your belly
with the iron hook he has...

01:28.520 --> 01:31.512
instead of a right hand,
at which time...

01:31.590 --> 01:35.117
his eyes turn red.

01:36.228 --> 01:38.161
"Girlie," said Hook,

01:38.229 --> 01:40.493
"we have come
for ye glass slippers."

01:40.565 --> 01:44.524
Who be you to order me about
and call me girlie?
<i>Take that.!</i>

01:44.602 --> 01:46.831
Take that! Take that!

01:49.206 --> 01:51.197
<i>Commoner.!</i>

01:51.274 --> 01:54.141
- <i>[Girl]</i>
<i>Hook came at her.</i>
- [Screaming]

01:54.211 --> 01:55.906
[Gasps]

01:55.979 --> 01:58.071
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>What happened then?</i>
<i>What happened then?</i>

01:58.147 --> 02:01.378
<i>[Girl]</i>
<i>The brave Cinderella settled</i>
<i>the matter once and for all...</i>

02:01.450 --> 02:04.317
<i>with her revolver.</i>
<i>With her revolver?</i>

02:04.386 --> 02:06.683
<i>[Woman Narrating]</i>
<i>The night on which</i>
<i>the extraordinary adventures...</i>

02:06.754 --> 02:09.484
<i>of these children</i>
<i>may be said to have begun...</i>

02:09.556 --> 02:12.424
<i>was the night Nana</i>
<i>barked at the window.</i>

02:12.494 --> 02:15.952
<i>But there was nothing there,</i>
<i>not a bird or a leaf.</i>

02:16.030 --> 02:18.020
<i>So the children forgot</i>
<i>about it,</i>

02:18.098 --> 02:21.864
<i>for what troubles a grown-up</i>
<i>will never trouble a child.</i>

02:21.935 --> 02:23.869
- [Cuckooing]
- [All Gasp]

02:26.273 --> 02:29.241
Oh, dearest George, dear Mary.
Oh, what a journey I've had.

02:31.777 --> 02:34.075
Bath time.

02:34.147 --> 02:36.911
- [Whooping]
- [Barks]

02:36.983 --> 02:39.280
[Screaming]

02:41.019 --> 02:44.284
<i>[Screaming Continues]</i>

02:44.356 --> 02:46.290
[Barks]
Not fair!

02:46.358 --> 02:50.760
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Not fair, indeed. But Nana was</i>
<i>the finest nurse on four paws.</i>

02:50.828 --> 02:53.592
No. No, I will not
forgive you.
<i>**[Piano]</i>

02:53.931 --> 02:57.627
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>There never was</i>
<i>a happier, simpler family.</i>

02:57.700 --> 03:02.899
<i>Mr. Darling was a banker</i>
<i>who knew the cost of everything,</i>
<i>even a hug.</i>

03:02.972 --> 03:06.635
<i>Mrs. Darling was the loveliest</i>
<i>lady in Bloomsbury...</i>

03:06.709 --> 03:10.872
<i>with a sweet, mocking mouth</i>
<i>that had one kiss on it...</i>

03:10.946 --> 03:12.971
<i>that Wendy could never get.</i>

03:13.048 --> 03:15.175
<i>Though there it was,</i>

03:15.250 --> 03:19.310
<i>perfectly conspicuous</i>
<i>on the right-hand corner.</i>

03:20.555 --> 03:23.046
<i>And sometimes there</i>
<i>was Aunt Millicent...</i>

03:23.124 --> 03:26.321
<i>who felt a dog for a nurse</i>
<i>lowered the whole tone</i>
<i>of the neighborhood.</i>

03:26.394 --> 03:29.556
All right, all right,
all right, all right.
Less noise.

03:29.629 --> 03:32.894
- Let's settle down.
This is not a farm.
- [Whines]

03:32.966 --> 03:35.662
- <i>[Millicent]</i>
<i>Bravo, George. Bravo.</i>
- Wendy's turn.

03:35.735 --> 03:39.295
Wendy must tell a story.
** [Piano]

03:39.371 --> 03:42.306
<i>Cecco, who carved his name</i>
<i>on the governor at Goa.</i>

03:42.374 --> 03:46.003
<i>Noodler, with his hands</i>
<i>on backwards.</i>

03:46.078 --> 03:47.807
- Heavens.
- Hook!

03:47.880 --> 03:52.441
- Hook?
- Hook, whose eyes turn red
as he guts you.

03:52.517 --> 03:55.350
Upon my soul, how children
are educated nowadays.

03:55.420 --> 03:58.320
- [Chuckles]
- I'm afraid I am not
learned at all, Aunt.

03:58.388 --> 04:01.186
- But I do know a thing or two
about pirates.
- Ooh.

04:01.258 --> 04:05.627
My unfulfilled ambition is
to write a great novel in three
parts about my adventures.

04:05.696 --> 04:08.596
- What adventures?
- I've yet to have them,

04:08.664 --> 04:10.598
but they will be
perfectly thrilling.

04:10.666 --> 04:14.261
But, child, novelists
are not highly thought of
in good society.

04:14.337 --> 04:17.829
And there is nothing
so difficult to marry as a novelist.

04:17.906 --> 04:19.702
- Marry?
- Marry?

04:19.774 --> 04:23.335
- Marry?
- But, Aunt, Wendy is not yet 13.

04:25.113 --> 04:27.877
Walk toward me, dear,
that I may appraise you.

04:27.949 --> 04:30.109
<i>[Mr. Darling]</i>
<i>Go on.</i>

04:30.184 --> 04:33.779
Walk to your auntie.
Stand up straight.
[Giggling]

04:33.854 --> 04:35.617
[Whines]

04:36.957 --> 04:40.221
- Stop it!
- Turn around.

04:40.293 --> 04:42.784
<i>[Laughter Continues]</i>

04:42.862 --> 04:44.887
Shh.

04:44.964 --> 04:47.296
Mm, yes.

04:47.367 --> 04:49.960
Oh, it's quite as I expected.

04:50.035 --> 04:53.163
Wendy possesses a woman's chin.

04:55.474 --> 04:59.341
Have you not noticed?
Observe her mouth.

04:59.410 --> 05:02.379
<i>There, hidden</i>
<i>in the right-hand corner,</i>

05:04.382 --> 05:06.043
is that a kiss?

05:06.117 --> 05:08.176
<i>[Mrs. Darling Gasps]</i>

05:08.252 --> 05:11.084
- A kiss?
- Like Mother's kiss.

05:11.154 --> 05:15.215
- <i>[Millicent]</i>
<i>A hidden kiss.</i>
- But what is it for?

05:16.559 --> 05:19.186
It is for the greatest
adventure of all.

05:19.261 --> 05:21.422
They that find it...

05:21.497 --> 05:24.660
have slipped in and out of heaven.

05:24.733 --> 05:26.667
Find what?

05:26.735 --> 05:30.101
The one the kiss belongs to.

05:31.272 --> 05:33.206
My Wendy...

05:33.274 --> 05:36.402
a woman.
Almost a woman.

05:36.477 --> 05:38.775
She must spend less time
with her brothers...

05:38.846 --> 05:41.109
<i>and more time with me.</i>
[All Gasp]

05:41.181 --> 05:43.547
She must have her own room.

05:43.617 --> 05:47.018
<i>Ayoung lady's room.</i>
Leave the...

05:47.087 --> 05:50.920
George, the daughter
of a clerk cannot hope to marry
as well as that of a manager.

05:50.990 --> 05:53.982
You must attend more parties,

05:54.060 --> 05:57.223
make small talk with
your superiors at the bank.

05:57.296 --> 06:00.287
Wit is very fashionable
at the moment.

06:00.365 --> 06:02.959
Wit.

06:03.468 --> 06:06.699
[Snoring]

06:25.288 --> 06:27.085
[Gasps]

06:27.156 --> 06:29.919
- <i>[Barking]</i>
- [Gasps]

06:33.161 --> 06:37.393
- [Screams]
- [Growling]

06:39.034 --> 06:40.933
[Gasps]

06:41.001 --> 06:44.164
[Barking]

06:52.345 --> 06:54.176
[Growling]
[Moans]

07:04.857 --> 07:07.655
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>But there was no sign of a body,</i>

07:07.726 --> 07:10.194
<i>for none had fallen.</i>

07:10.262 --> 07:13.321
<i>Certainly she had been dreaming.</i>

07:23.673 --> 07:26.699
- [Loud Bang]
- [Gasps]

07:26.777 --> 07:29.507
If this is you in bed,

07:29.579 --> 07:32.809
what is this?

07:33.883 --> 07:35.646
A boy.

07:35.718 --> 07:40.553
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Miss Fulsom dispatched a letter</i>
<i>of outrage to Mr. Darling...</i>

07:40.623 --> 07:42.852
<i>that set new standards</i>
<i>of prudery, even for her.</i>

07:42.924 --> 07:45.119
Yes, miss.

07:46.628 --> 07:52.065
<i>Mr. Darling had been practicing</i>
<i>small talk all afternoon.</i>

07:52.132 --> 07:55.158
I say, it's nice weather we're having.

07:55.235 --> 07:57.226
<i>And now his opportunity had arrived.</i>

07:57.304 --> 08:01.501
<i>Sir Edward Quiller Couch,</i>
<i>the president of the bank,</i>

08:01.574 --> 08:03.804
<i>was a man who enjoyed small talk...</i>

08:03.876 --> 08:06.344
<i>almost as much</i>
<i>as a good balance sheet.</i>

08:07.880 --> 08:10.815
<i>Wendy walked as one condemned.</i>

08:10.883 --> 08:13.544
<i>And then... fate.</i>
[Bell Rings]

08:15.387 --> 08:19.050
The letter! Wait! Stop!

08:19.124 --> 08:21.421
[Michael]
Wendy, wait!
Come back!

08:23.661 --> 08:26.425
I say, what a splendid tie.
[Mumbles]

08:28.165 --> 08:31.656
<i>Wait.! You there.! Stop.!</i>

08:31.734 --> 08:34.760
- <i>Wendy.! Nana, come back.!</i>
- [Barking]

08:34.837 --> 08:38.774
<i>That's Â£200 saved.</i>
<i>Ajudicious investment?</i>

08:38.842 --> 08:41.605
Indeed.
Uh...

08:45.180 --> 08:49.514
Hi. Um...
[Muttering]

08:49.585 --> 08:51.882
I, uh...

08:51.953 --> 08:56.151
<i>You there, stop.! Wait.!</i>

08:56.224 --> 08:58.556
Stop! Wait!
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

08:58.626 --> 09:00.924
Uh, uh, uh... I, uh...

09:00.995 --> 09:02.723
<i>[Stammering]</i>

09:02.796 --> 09:05.196
<i>[Pounding]</i>
<i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>Father.!</i>

09:07.934 --> 09:10.198
<i>I can explain.!</i>

09:15.941 --> 09:17.636
No!

09:20.946 --> 09:23.277
[Grunts]

09:25.116 --> 09:27.311
[All Screaming]

09:27.385 --> 09:30.718
<i>[Crash]</i>

09:30.788 --> 09:32.914
[Men Grumbling]
<i>[Mr. Darling]</i>
<i>I have been humiliated.!</i>

09:32.990 --> 09:34.924
[Wendy Chattering]
No!

09:34.992 --> 09:38.792
I must become a man
that children fear
and adults respect,

09:38.862 --> 09:41.330
or we shall all
end up in the street!

09:41.398 --> 09:43.661
George, not so loud.
The neighbors will hear.

09:43.733 --> 09:47.464
Let them hear.
Let the whole world know!

09:47.537 --> 09:51.268
This is not a nurse! This is a dog.

09:51.340 --> 09:53.569
[Whining]

09:54.910 --> 09:57.470
[Gasps]

09:57.546 --> 10:00.276
Tomorrow you begin
your instruction...

10:00.348 --> 10:03.316
<i>with Aunt Millicent.</i>

10:03.384 --> 10:05.614
<i>It's time for you to grow up.!</i>

10:09.290 --> 10:11.622
<i>[Barking]</i>

10:16.496 --> 10:18.862
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Mother?</i>

10:18.932 --> 10:22.163
Can anything harm us
after the night-lights are lit?

10:22.235 --> 10:24.566
No, precious.

10:24.636 --> 10:29.096
They are the eyes a mother
leaves behind to guard her children.

10:33.978 --> 10:36.811
Mother, must you go
to the party?

10:36.881 --> 10:39.315
Please, Mother.
Yes, Mother,
you don't have to go.

10:39.383 --> 10:41.317
Father can go by himself.
Please, Mother.

10:41.385 --> 10:43.648
By himself?

10:43.720 --> 10:46.450
Your father is a brave man.

10:46.523 --> 10:50.459
But he's going to need
the special kiss to face
his colleagues tonight.

10:50.527 --> 10:52.654
Father? Brave?

10:54.797 --> 10:58.164
There are many
different kinds of bravery.

10:58.233 --> 11:02.169
There's the bravery of thinking
of others before oneself.

11:02.237 --> 11:07.230
Now, your father has never
brandished a sword nor fired
a pistol, thank heavens.

11:09.210 --> 11:13.044
But he's made many sacrifices
for his family...

11:13.114 --> 11:16.014
and put away many dreams.

11:16.083 --> 11:18.779
Where did he put them?

11:18.852 --> 11:21.116
He put them in a drawer.

11:21.188 --> 11:26.056
And sometimes, late at night,
we take them out and admire them.

11:27.727 --> 11:31.060
<i>But it gets harder and harder</i>
<i>to close the drawer.</i>

11:32.965 --> 11:34.955
He does.

11:36.534 --> 11:38.695
And that is why he is brave.

11:42.407 --> 11:44.567
And remember, every cloud
has a silver lining.

11:44.642 --> 11:48.100
Oh.
Oh. No, it's snowing.

11:48.178 --> 11:50.976
Oh, we'll catch our death.
Better death than gossip.

11:51.048 --> 11:54.676
You will enter that drawing room
with your head held high.

12:14.002 --> 12:17.596
[Hinge Squeaking]

12:25.211 --> 12:27.145
[Squealing]

12:32.886 --> 12:35.718
[High-Pitched Chattering]

12:37.456 --> 12:39.048
[Gasps]

12:57.240 --> 12:59.606
Oh!
[Grunts]

13:08.250 --> 13:10.411
[Chattering]

13:16.091 --> 13:18.924
[Chattering Continues]

13:18.993 --> 13:21.188
Shh!

13:22.197 --> 13:24.688
One, two,

13:24.766 --> 13:27.962
<i>[Bell Jingling]</i>
Three!

13:28.035 --> 13:30.629
[Gasps]
Aha!

13:33.107 --> 13:36.701
[High-Pitched Scream]
Come here, you!

13:36.776 --> 13:38.869
I got you.

13:38.945 --> 13:40.776
[Gasps]

13:40.847 --> 13:43.372
- [Shouts]
- [Shrieking]

13:47.586 --> 13:50.146
Ha!

13:50.222 --> 13:52.816
[Gasps]

14:32.160 --> 14:34.151
[Gasps]

14:36.797 --> 14:38.788
[Gasps]

14:48.073 --> 14:50.439
[Grunting]

14:50.509 --> 14:52.670
[Panting]

15:03.421 --> 15:05.787
Boy, why are you crying?
[Gasps]

15:05.857 --> 15:08.120
You can fly!

15:24.607 --> 15:26.972
What is your name?
What is your name?

15:27.042 --> 15:29.738
Wendy Moira Angela Darling.

15:29.811 --> 15:32.143
Peter... Pan.

15:32.214 --> 15:34.148
Where do you live?

15:34.216 --> 15:38.049
Second to the right and then
straight on till morning.
[Gasps]

15:38.118 --> 15:40.609
They put that on the letters?
Don't get any letters.

15:40.688 --> 15:43.418
But your mother gets letters.
Don't have a mother.

15:45.025 --> 15:48.926
No wonder you were crying.
I wasn't crying
about mothers.

15:48.995 --> 15:52.863
I was crying because I can't
get the shadow to stick.

15:52.932 --> 15:55.423
And I wasn't crying!

15:58.904 --> 16:01.998
[Chuckles]

16:02.074 --> 16:05.066
I could sew it on for you.

16:10.147 --> 16:13.241
[Grunts]

16:14.385 --> 16:16.615
This may hurt a little.

16:19.322 --> 16:22.018
[Groaning]

16:24.160 --> 16:27.993
- [Loud Groan]
- Might I borrow your knife?

16:33.669 --> 16:36.638
[Whimpers]

16:38.206 --> 16:41.869
- Thank you.
- [Mimicking, Growls]

16:52.352 --> 16:54.047
[Chuckles]

16:54.121 --> 16:58.056
- Oh, the cleverness of me!
- Of course, I did nothing.

16:58.124 --> 17:00.217
Aw, you did a little.
<i>A little?</i>

17:04.329 --> 17:06.662
Good night.

17:11.502 --> 17:13.493
Wendy?

17:14.906 --> 17:17.670
One girl is worth more
than 20 boys.

17:17.742 --> 17:20.039
<i>You really think so?</i>

17:20.109 --> 17:24.240
I live with boys... the Lost Boys.
They are well named.

17:24.315 --> 17:26.806
[Gasps]
Who are they?

17:26.884 --> 17:29.647
Children who fall out of their prams
when the nurse is not looking.

17:29.719 --> 17:32.347
If they are not claimed in seven days,
they are sent to the Neverland.

17:32.422 --> 17:36.825
- Are there girls too?
- Girls are much too clever
to fall out of their prams.

17:36.893 --> 17:41.625
Peter, it is perfectly lovely
the way you talk about girls.

17:44.366 --> 17:47.529
I should like to give you...

17:47.602 --> 17:49.535
a... kiss.

17:51.505 --> 17:54.235
Don't you know what a kiss is?

17:54.308 --> 17:56.367
I shall know when you give me one.

18:08.455 --> 18:10.581
I suppose
I'm to give you one now.

18:10.656 --> 18:12.783
If you like.

18:24.235 --> 18:26.226
[Clears Throat]

18:34.177 --> 18:36.202
Thank you.

18:38.081 --> 18:40.640
How old are you, Peter?
Quite young.

18:40.716 --> 18:44.447
- Don't you know?
- I ran away.

18:44.520 --> 18:49.422
One night, I heard my mother
and father talking of what
I was to be when I became a man.

18:51.493 --> 18:55.327
So I ran away to Kensington
Gardens and I met Tink.
[Squealing]

18:55.397 --> 18:58.332
- Tink?
- Tinker Bell.

18:58.400 --> 19:00.264
She's my fairy.

19:00.334 --> 19:05.431
- But there's no such thing as...
- Don't say that.

19:05.506 --> 19:09.135
Every time somebody
says that, a fairy
somewhere falls down dead.

19:09.209 --> 19:11.733
And I shall never find her
if she's dead.

19:11.811 --> 19:15.542
You don't mean to tell me
there's a fairy in this room.

19:15.615 --> 19:18.311
<i>We come to listen</i>
<i>to the stories.</i>
[Grunts]

19:18.384 --> 19:22.217
I like the one about the prince
who couldn't find the lady
who wore glass slippers.

19:22.287 --> 19:25.120
<i>Cinderella.</i>

19:25.190 --> 19:30.491
<i>Peter, he found her</i>
<i>and they</i>...<i>and they...</i>

19:32.530 --> 19:35.795
lived happily ever after.

19:35.866 --> 19:39.029
I knew it.
Peter.

19:40.970 --> 19:43.996
I should like to give you...

19:44.074 --> 19:48.340
a... thimble.

19:48.411 --> 19:50.139
What's that?

19:52.414 --> 19:54.609
[Growls]

19:57.219 --> 19:59.517
- <i>[Screaming]</i>
- Tink!

20:02.457 --> 20:06.120
<i>Tink.! Tink, no.!</i>

20:08.196 --> 20:10.164
[Chattering]

20:10.230 --> 20:12.858
She's not very polite.

20:14.201 --> 20:17.295
<i>She says if you try to</i>
<i>give me a thimble again,</i>

20:19.539 --> 20:21.335
she'll kill you.
Oh.

20:22.408 --> 20:27.243
And I had supposed fairies
to be charming.
[Blows Raspberry]

20:27.313 --> 20:30.873
Peter, don't go.
I have to tell the others
about Cinderella.

20:30.949 --> 20:35.648
- But I know lots of stories,
stories I could tell the boys.
- Come with me.

20:35.720 --> 20:39.178
L... I cannot fly.
<i>I'll teach you.</i>

20:39.257 --> 20:43.454
I'll teach you to ride the wind's back.
And away we go.

20:45.395 --> 20:47.886
Could John and Michael come too?

20:47.965 --> 20:51.923
[Snoring]

20:55.671 --> 20:58.401
- Michael! Michael!
- [Grunts]

20:58.474 --> 21:01.442
- John! John!
- I didn't do it.

21:01.510 --> 21:05.105
There is a boy here
who is to teach us to fly.

21:05.180 --> 21:08.741
You offend reason, sir.

21:09.918 --> 21:11.509
Mm-hmm.

21:21.928 --> 21:23.623
I should like to
offend it with you.

21:23.696 --> 21:28.690
You just think happy thoughts,
and they lift you into the air.
[Chuckles]

21:31.803 --> 21:33.737
It's easy.

21:33.805 --> 21:37.206
I've got it! I've got it!

21:37.276 --> 21:41.144
Swords, daggers, Napoleon!

21:41.213 --> 21:44.773
- <i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>Stand back.</i>
- Yahoo!

21:44.849 --> 21:46.908
[Screaming]

21:46.984 --> 21:49.111
[Grunts]
John!

21:49.187 --> 21:52.622
- [Groans]
- [Laughing]

21:54.157 --> 21:57.422
[Gasps]
<i>Wendy.! Wendy.! Watch me.!</i>

21:57.494 --> 22:02.123
Puddings, mud pies, ice cream,
never to take a bath again!

22:02.198 --> 22:04.962
[Screaming]
<i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>Michael.!</i>

22:06.202 --> 22:08.466
[Barking]

22:10.806 --> 22:13.171
Whoa!

22:22.749 --> 22:26.310
[Gasps, Giggling]

22:31.225 --> 22:34.990
Come away.
Come away to Neverland.

22:35.061 --> 22:37.461
Oh. What about Mother?

22:38.531 --> 22:40.761
Father?
Nana?

22:42.567 --> 22:44.762
- There are mermaids.
- Mermaids?

22:44.836 --> 22:47.202
Indians!
[Both]
Indians?

22:47.272 --> 22:50.571
- Pirates!
- [Both]
Pirates?

22:50.642 --> 22:53.474
Whoa-ho!

22:53.544 --> 22:56.206
<i>John, wait for me.!</i>

22:57.448 --> 22:59.848
[Barking]

22:59.917 --> 23:03.044
[Chattering]

23:04.387 --> 23:06.446
[Chuckling]

23:06.522 --> 23:08.956
[Laughing]

23:11.027 --> 23:13.824
<i>May I introduce my wife...</i>

23:13.895 --> 23:15.362
Mary?
Mary.

23:15.430 --> 23:17.830
Mary.

23:17.899 --> 23:20.299
<i>Delighted.</i>
Thank you, Sir Edward.

23:20.369 --> 23:22.132
<i>[Barking]</i>
<i>[Banging]</i>

23:22.204 --> 23:25.661
- [Guests Gasping]
- [Gasps]

23:47.226 --> 23:51.492
Forget them, Wendy.
Forget them all.

23:51.563 --> 23:56.556
Come with me where you'll never,
never have to worry about
grown-up things again.

23:57.969 --> 24:01.598
What is it? What's wrong?

24:03.473 --> 24:06.670
Never is an awfully long time.

24:11.348 --> 24:15.408
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>It would be delightful to report</i>
<i>that they reached the nursery in time.</i>

24:18.587 --> 24:20.578
<i>But then there</i>
<i>would be no story.</i>

24:22.158 --> 24:25.149
[Michael, John Shouting]

24:26.761 --> 24:28.695
[Laughing]

24:38.005 --> 24:40.803
[Shouting]

24:40.874 --> 24:43.399
[Woman]
But you're covered
in dog hair, my darling.

24:43.477 --> 24:47.242
- [Peter] Hello, old chap.
- [Wendy] Good evening.

24:47.313 --> 24:48.974
[John]
Thank you.

24:49.048 --> 24:51.642
Whoa-ho!

24:51.718 --> 24:55.244
[Shouting]
Higher!

24:55.320 --> 24:57.254
[Shouting]

25:08.199 --> 25:10.292
Who are you?

25:10.368 --> 25:12.893
I'm John.

25:12.970 --> 25:15.597
[Chattering]
John.

25:15.672 --> 25:19.267
Take hold of this.
Ta-da!

25:21.077 --> 25:23.170
Both hands.

25:27.383 --> 25:29.817
[John Shouting]
Pass it on.

25:29.885 --> 25:33.082
Michael, take hold of my ankle.

25:33.155 --> 25:36.282
Wendy, take hold of my ankle!

25:36.357 --> 25:39.622
<i>And whatever happens,</i>
<i>don't... let...</i>

25:39.694 --> 25:42.185
go!
[All Screaming]

26:19.096 --> 26:21.758
<i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>Neverland.</i>

26:35.343 --> 26:38.141
<i>[Birds Twittering]</i>

26:38.213 --> 26:40.704
<i>[Men]</i>
<i>*Lying, thieving</i>
<i>a life of sin *</i>

26:40.782 --> 26:43.751
<i>*Apirating we go *</i>

26:43.819 --> 26:47.379
<i>* We're sure to meet below *</i>

26:47.455 --> 26:50.618
* Fire the cannons
Pour the rum *

26:50.691 --> 26:53.922
* Deal the cards
For night has come *

26:53.994 --> 26:56.518
* A pirating we go **

26:56.596 --> 26:59.258
[Grunting]

26:59.332 --> 27:01.994
[Snoring]

27:08.307 --> 27:10.798
[Squawking]
[Screaming]

27:10.876 --> 27:13.401
Devil bird!

27:14.713 --> 27:17.180
[Sighing]

27:19.317 --> 27:21.785
<i>[Rumbling]</i>

27:28.325 --> 27:31.089
[Men Shouting]

27:36.165 --> 27:38.030
<i>Cap'n?</i>

27:43.205 --> 27:47.504
Cap'n? As I was sitting
wide-eyed on my watch,

27:47.575 --> 27:50.942
I noticed it was
wintertime on the water
and springtime on the shore.

27:51.012 --> 27:54.038
I says to meself,
"That's early for spring to be astir.

27:54.115 --> 27:56.275
Spring's not due till 3:00 p.m."

27:56.350 --> 27:59.251
Check the time yourself,
Cap'n, and then tell...

28:09.328 --> 28:14.288
I was dreaming, Smee, of Pan.

28:14.367 --> 28:16.130
Pan, Cap'n?

28:16.202 --> 28:18.863
And in my dream,

28:18.937 --> 28:22.304
I was a magnanimous fellow...

28:23.475 --> 28:25.670
full of forgiveness.

28:26.977 --> 28:28.911
I thanked Pan...

28:28.979 --> 28:31.072
<i>for cutting off my hand...</i>

28:31.148 --> 28:34.049
and for giving me
this fine hook...

28:34.118 --> 28:38.952
for disemboweling
and ripping throats...

28:39.022 --> 28:42.321
and other such homely uses...

28:42.392 --> 28:45.520
as combing my hair.

28:45.595 --> 28:47.528
[Groans]

28:47.596 --> 28:50.565
So, Pan did you
a favor then, Cap'n?
A favor?

28:53.068 --> 28:56.299
He threw my hand
to a crocodile.

28:56.371 --> 28:59.931
The beast liked it so much,
it's followed me ever since,

29:00.007 --> 29:02.635
licking its lips
for the rest of me.

29:02.710 --> 29:05.201
[Shouting]
You call that a favor?

29:05.279 --> 29:07.644
No. No. No. No.

29:12.886 --> 29:17.117
Thank you.
Thank Lucifer the beast
swallowed a clock.

29:17.189 --> 29:21.125
<i>If it wasn't for the ticking,</i>
<i>it'd have had me by now.</i>

29:21.193 --> 29:25.687
[Groans]
Why did you wake me, Smee?

29:25.764 --> 29:29.790
Like I said, Cap'n,
the ice is melting.

29:29.867 --> 29:33.997
The sun is out.
And the flowers are all in bloom.

29:34.072 --> 29:36.006
He's back.

29:46.450 --> 29:48.508
[Chattering]

29:53.656 --> 29:55.647
Forty gunner.

29:55.725 --> 29:58.420
<i>She must do 12 knots</i>
<i>under full sail.</i>

30:03.698 --> 30:06.223
<i>[Gasps]</i>
<i>Noodler, with his hands</i>
<i>on backwards.!</i>

30:06.301 --> 30:09.667
BillJukes!
Every inch of him tattooed.

30:11.438 --> 30:13.235
<i>[Gasps]</i>
<i>Hook.!</i>

30:18.578 --> 30:21.069
[Whispering]
Let's take a closer look.

30:22.615 --> 30:26.278
Yahoo!
[Wendy]
Peter!

30:26.352 --> 30:28.478
Watch this.

30:28.553 --> 30:30.885
Whoa-ho-ho!

30:30.956 --> 30:32.947
[Shouting Continues]

30:33.025 --> 30:34.959
[John]
Whoa! My hat!

30:35.027 --> 30:37.495
Ugly Smee!
Ugly, fat Smee!

30:37.562 --> 30:39.995
[Squawks]
Solar eclipse.

30:40.064 --> 30:42.089
<i>Dark in here.</i>
<i>Let me out. Let me out.!</i>

30:42.166 --> 30:45.294
<i>[Squawks]</i>
<i>Can't see.</i>

30:45.369 --> 30:48.360
<i>Dark in here. Candle.</i>

30:48.438 --> 30:51.202
<i>I need candle. Help.! Help.!</i>

30:57.847 --> 30:59.780
Fetch Long Tom.

31:00.949 --> 31:02.780
Fire!

31:03.819 --> 31:06.788
[Screaming]

31:06.855 --> 31:10.381
- Help! Help!
- [Laughing]

31:13.628 --> 31:16.290
[Grunts]
[John, Michael Screaming]

31:20.500 --> 31:23.992
Tink, find Wendy.
Leave the rest to me.

31:24.071 --> 31:26.596
Wendy.

31:26.673 --> 31:28.970
Oh, Captain Hook!

31:29.041 --> 31:31.441
Pan!

31:31.510 --> 31:34.843
Stay with him!
You can't catch me.

31:34.914 --> 31:37.849
<i>Over here.!</i>
Fire!

31:38.850 --> 31:40.579
<i>[Pan Laughing]</i>

31:41.686 --> 31:44.086
Timber!

31:44.155 --> 31:46.521
[Both]
Whoa!

31:46.591 --> 31:48.491
Michael, are you shot?

31:48.560 --> 31:51.960
I haven't checked yet!
But there's something worser!

31:52.029 --> 31:54.259
Oh, what could be worse?

31:54.331 --> 31:59.165
My thoughts aren't very happy!

31:59.235 --> 32:01.863
Happy thoughts!

32:01.938 --> 32:05.305
Happy thoughts.
<i>What would Mom and Dad do?</i>

32:05.374 --> 32:09.309
Napoleon!
<i>[Hook]</i>
<i>Damnation.!</i>

32:09.377 --> 32:12.505
Reload the cannon! Quickly!

32:12.581 --> 32:16.517
Reload the cannon?
But, Cap'n, he is gone.
<i>[Hook Piercing Flesh]</i>

32:18.253 --> 32:20.948
Any other contributions?

32:21.021 --> 32:23.990
Search the jungle!
Bring me those children!

32:24.191 --> 32:27.285
<i>[Boy] What is it?</i>
<i>[Boy #2]</i>
<i>It's a large white bird.</i>

32:27.361 --> 32:29.658
Quite ugly too. No!
Give me it!

32:29.729 --> 32:32.220
When Peter's away,
I'm in charge!

32:32.298 --> 32:34.528
I get to look
through the telescope.

32:34.601 --> 32:36.694
<i>It's coming closer.</i>
[Squeals]

32:36.770 --> 32:40.296
[Gasps]
My God, I've gone blind!
[Laughing]

32:40.372 --> 32:42.397
[Mimicking]
I'm blind. I've gone blind.
I'm blind.

32:42.474 --> 32:44.704
Hello, Tink. Where's Peter?

32:44.777 --> 32:46.972
[Both]
Hello, Tink.
She's blinded me!

32:47.045 --> 32:48.979
Hello, Tink.
Hello, Tink.

32:49.047 --> 32:52.743
- Any more news of Cinderella?
- [Chatters]

32:55.319 --> 32:57.685
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Now, Tinker Bell was not all bad.</i>

32:57.755 --> 33:00.188
<i>Sometimes she was all good.</i>

33:00.257 --> 33:03.624
<i>But fairies are so small they only</i>
<i>have room for one feeling at a time.</i>

33:03.693 --> 33:07.959
Tink says the bird's
called a..."Wendy."

33:08.031 --> 33:11.158
And Peter wants us to...
[Gasps]

33:15.738 --> 33:18.002
Oh, Peter! Oh!

33:18.073 --> 33:20.404
Shoot it down.

33:23.044 --> 33:25.842
Well, we have our orders.
Shoot the Wendy bird.

33:25.914 --> 33:27.939
[All]
Aye, aye!

33:28.016 --> 33:30.347
Ready? Aim!

33:30.417 --> 33:33.079
- [Gasps]
- Fire!

33:33.153 --> 33:35.280
Bye-bye!

33:35.355 --> 33:37.949
<i>Three, two,</i>

33:38.025 --> 33:40.186
<i>one.!</i>

33:40.260 --> 33:42.625
[All Gasp]

33:45.898 --> 33:48.799
I got it. I got it!

33:48.868 --> 33:51.267
[All Shouting]

33:56.975 --> 33:59.034
[Laughing]

34:03.080 --> 34:05.310
That is no bird.

34:06.717 --> 34:10.619
It is a lady.
[Both]
And Tootles...

34:10.688 --> 34:13.281
[All]
Tootles has killed her.

34:13.356 --> 34:17.224
Ha! I'm back! Great news.
I know what happened
to Cinderella.

34:17.293 --> 34:22.161
She defeated the pirates.
There was stabbing, slicing,
torturing, bleeding...

34:22.231 --> 34:24.665
<i>and they lived happily ever after.</i>

34:24.733 --> 34:28.601
Well, that's a relief,
I must say.
<i>Greater news.!</i>

34:28.670 --> 34:32.469
I have brought you she
that told of Cinderella.
She is to tell us stories!

34:32.540 --> 34:34.804
She is...

34:36.510 --> 34:39.342
Dead.

34:39.413 --> 34:41.437
Tragic.

34:41.514 --> 34:43.812
Awful.
Good shot, though.

34:46.887 --> 34:50.014
Whose arrow?

34:58.898 --> 35:00.957
Mine, Peter.

35:03.167 --> 35:05.101
Strike, Peter.

35:05.169 --> 35:07.194
<i>Strike true.</i>

35:12.342 --> 35:14.276
[Moans]

35:14.344 --> 35:16.471
- The Wendy lives!
- [Screams]

35:26.722 --> 35:29.486
It's my kiss.

35:29.558 --> 35:32.025
My kiss saved her.

35:32.093 --> 35:34.857
I remember kisses.

35:34.930 --> 35:36.921
Let me see it.

35:38.266 --> 35:42.395
Aye, that is a kiss.
A powerful thing.

35:42.469 --> 35:45.734
Let us carry her down
to the house.

35:45.806 --> 35:47.967
Hands.

35:49.944 --> 35:51.878
They're a bit dirty.

35:51.946 --> 35:53.970
<i>She must stay here and die.</i>

35:54.047 --> 35:57.016
No!
Oh, how could I have
thought that? Stupid.

35:57.083 --> 35:59.017
Sorry.

36:01.421 --> 36:03.854
We shall build
a house around her.

36:03.922 --> 36:06.083
[All Cheering, Chattering]
With a chimney!

36:06.158 --> 36:08.991
And a door knocker!
And windows!

36:16.000 --> 36:18.025
[Both Whispering]
Tink did it.

36:24.607 --> 36:28.043
<i>Tinker Bell?</i>
<i>Oh, Tinker Bell?</i>
[Squeaks]

36:33.182 --> 36:37.278
- Was it you, Tink?
- Hallelujah. Hallelujah.

36:38.921 --> 36:42.118
[Snickering,
Chattering]

36:42.191 --> 36:45.648
Then I am your friend no more.

36:53.233 --> 36:55.667
[Whimpers]

37:06.045 --> 37:09.208
<i>[Chuckling, Gasps]</i>

37:11.884 --> 37:13.908
<i>[Chattering]</i>

37:13.985 --> 37:17.682
<i>First impressions</i>
<i>are very, very important.</i>
<i>[Hammering]</i>

37:17.756 --> 37:20.247
<i>Here she is.</i>
<i>Look loveable.</i>

37:23.028 --> 37:28.124
<i>Wendy lady, for you we built</i>
<i>this house with a door knocker.</i>

37:28.198 --> 37:30.462
And a chimney.
One, two, three.

37:30.534 --> 37:33.297
[All]
Please be our mother.

37:36.372 --> 37:38.431
Oh.

37:38.508 --> 37:41.875
Well, it is frightfully fascinating.

37:41.944 --> 37:44.776
But, you see,
I've had no real experience.

37:46.114 --> 37:48.844
Do you tell stories?
Yes.

37:48.917 --> 37:52.011
Then you're perfect.
Very well.

37:52.087 --> 37:55.112
- I will do my best.
- Hooray!

37:55.189 --> 37:58.784
[All Chattering At Once]
Sorry about the blindfold.

37:58.859 --> 38:01.726
We must be cautious.
There are some nasty
characters about.

38:01.796 --> 38:04.025
If Hook discovers our hideout,
he'll gut us.

38:04.097 --> 38:07.362
How dreadful!
Oh, we live for it!

38:10.970 --> 38:13.700
But l...
Time to meet Father, Mother.

38:15.474 --> 38:18.602
So looking forward
to being your son.

38:22.281 --> 38:24.441
[Screams]

38:24.515 --> 38:26.847
[Both Grunt]

38:26.918 --> 38:28.977
Welcome, Mother.

38:29.053 --> 38:31.749
Discipline. That's what
fathers believe in.

38:31.823 --> 38:36.418
You must spank the children immediately
before they try to kill you again.

38:36.493 --> 38:39.121
In fact, we should kill them.

38:42.732 --> 38:44.665
[Shouting]
[All Screaming]

38:44.733 --> 38:47.099
Peter!

38:47.169 --> 38:49.228
Father!

38:49.305 --> 38:52.604
I agree that they
are perfectly horrid,

38:52.675 --> 38:56.872
but kill them
and they shall think
themselves important.

38:56.945 --> 38:59.311
So important.
And unique.

38:59.380 --> 39:03.248
I suggest something...

39:03.318 --> 39:05.615
far more dreadful.

39:08.555 --> 39:10.489
Medicine.

39:10.557 --> 39:13.754
It's the most beastly,
disgusting stuff.

39:13.827 --> 39:15.794
[Sniffs]

39:15.862 --> 39:19.161
The sticky, sweet kind.

39:19.232 --> 39:21.928
[All]
Kill us, please!
Kill us, please!

39:22.001 --> 39:25.026
Littlest first. Michael?

39:26.605 --> 39:31.406
- Michael. John. My brothers!
- Who?

39:32.077 --> 39:34.170
<i>[Animal Roaring]</i>

39:50.560 --> 39:52.585
Hello?

39:52.662 --> 39:55.425
<i>[Echoing]</i>
<i>Hello? Hello? Hello?</i>

40:00.002 --> 40:02.766
<i>[Ticking]</i>

40:04.573 --> 40:07.166
It's louder from inside
this rock.

40:08.843 --> 40:11.471
How very peculiar.

40:16.116 --> 40:19.108
[Low Growling]

40:21.454 --> 40:24.287
- [Roaring]
- [Screaming]

40:24.357 --> 40:28.053
<i>[John]</i>
<i>Happy thoughts.!</i>
<i>Swords, daggers, Napoleon.!</i>

40:28.127 --> 40:31.096
[Both Screaming]

40:31.163 --> 40:33.290
How humiliating.

40:35.367 --> 40:39.427
John, there's something worser.

40:42.774 --> 40:45.504
[Both Screaming]

40:52.983 --> 40:56.611
<i>Princess Tiger Lily.</i>

40:56.686 --> 40:58.278
[Gasps]

40:59.956 --> 41:03.585
<i>We search as ever for Peter Pan...</i>

41:03.659 --> 41:06.092
and his secret hideout.

41:07.696 --> 41:09.630
Luckily, two boys
of his acquaintance...

41:09.698 --> 41:13.134
<i>were seen falling</i>
<i>into this part of thejungle.</i>

41:14.369 --> 41:16.302
Have you seen them?

41:16.370 --> 41:20.170
[Speaking Foreign Language]

41:30.750 --> 41:33.150
She says,
"Sorry, but, no."

41:37.089 --> 41:41.617
My Hook thinks
you have, Princess.

41:41.693 --> 41:45.322
I say, unhand that savage, you...

41:45.397 --> 41:48.832
<i>you</i>...<i>you savage.!</i>

41:50.334 --> 41:53.633
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Now, mermaids are not</i>
<i>as they are in storybooks.</i>

41:53.704 --> 41:56.036
<i>They are dark creatures...</i>

41:56.107 --> 41:59.837
<i>in touch with all things mysterious.</i>

42:01.211 --> 42:03.975
<i>If Hook had captured</i>
<i>Wendy's brothers,</i>

42:04.047 --> 42:06.844
<i>the mermaids would know.</i>

42:06.915 --> 42:08.883
Oh, how sweet.

42:12.087 --> 42:15.318
Are mermaids not sweet?

42:15.391 --> 42:17.551
They'll sweetly drown you
if you get too close.

42:28.502 --> 42:31.164
[Clicking Tongues]

42:44.984 --> 42:47.781
- [Hisses]
- [Screeches]

42:51.222 --> 42:54.953
Hook has your brothers
at the Black Castle.

42:57.461 --> 43:00.055
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

43:18.213 --> 43:21.376
Like all surprise attacks,
it must be conducted...

43:22.718 --> 43:24.276
improperly.

43:24.353 --> 43:26.617
<i>Put the children on the rock.</i>

43:26.688 --> 43:28.552
** [Humming]

43:28.622 --> 43:31.216
[Laughing]

43:31.292 --> 43:34.784
Sorry, Your Highness.
Any last words?

43:34.862 --> 43:37.490
Beg for your lives.

43:37.565 --> 43:42.365
Sirs! My brother and I
are English gentlemen.

43:42.435 --> 43:45.131
English gentlemen do not beg.

43:45.205 --> 43:48.071
Please!

43:48.140 --> 43:51.132
Please! Please!
Please don't kill us!

43:51.210 --> 43:54.475
Please don't kill me, either.
I've never done anything...

43:54.546 --> 43:58.379
Aah! It's cold! It's cold!

44:00.051 --> 44:03.179
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Help.!</i>
Come on. Fly to the rescue,

44:03.254 --> 44:07.588
and then I'll shoot you right
through your noble intentions.

44:10.694 --> 44:14.186
I brought these.
Can you use it?

44:24.373 --> 44:29.207
Promise me one thing.
Leave Hook to me.

44:29.277 --> 44:31.541
I promise.

44:31.613 --> 44:35.413
- Wait here for my signal.
- Wait here?

44:35.483 --> 44:37.951
<i>Peter.!</i>

44:52.064 --> 44:57.468
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Thus Wendy first laid eyes on</i>
<i>the dark figure who haunted her stories.</i>

44:57.537 --> 45:01.336
<i>She saw the piercing eyes</i>
<i>and was not afraid,</i>

45:01.406 --> 45:03.897
<i>but entranced.</i>

45:03.975 --> 45:06.341
<i>[Men]</i>
<i>* We're sure to meet below *</i>

45:06.411 --> 45:08.379
[Laughing]

45:08.447 --> 45:12.075
<i>[Hook]</i>
<i>Mr. Smee?</i>

45:12.149 --> 45:15.209
That you, Cap'n?
<i>Brimstone and gall, man.</i>

45:15.286 --> 45:18.084
<i>What do you think you're doing?</i>

45:18.155 --> 45:21.123
Well, we've put the children
on the rope, Cap'n, like you said.

45:21.191 --> 45:24.854
<i>Set 'em free.!</i>
<i>Set 'em free?</i>

45:24.928 --> 45:29.830
- Well, what about your trap?
- Set them free, or
I'll plunge my hook in you.

45:29.898 --> 45:31.695
[Sword Clanging]

45:31.767 --> 45:34.395
[Gasps]

45:49.516 --> 45:53.111
I don't know what he wants with 'em.
I'm just a blithering idiot, aren't I?

45:53.186 --> 45:57.350
Chain 'em up. Let 'em go.

45:57.424 --> 46:00.756
- And take your cat with ya.
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>

46:03.496 --> 46:05.828
[Whispering
In Foreign Language]

46:10.401 --> 46:12.801
<i>Mr. Smee?</i>
Aye, Cap'n?

46:12.871 --> 46:15.567
- Any sign of him?
- No, Cap'n.

46:16.574 --> 46:18.872
Where are the children?

46:18.943 --> 46:21.433
It's all right, Cap'n.
We let 'em go.

46:21.512 --> 46:23.605
You what?

46:23.680 --> 46:25.648
We let 'em go.

46:27.084 --> 46:30.780
- [Chuckling]
- [Both Laughing]

46:37.293 --> 46:41.626
You... let... them... go.

46:52.840 --> 46:55.775
- [Hook's Voice]
Mr. Smee!
- [Screaming]

46:55.843 --> 46:58.641
Who are you, stranger?

46:58.712 --> 47:02.613
<i>I am James Hook,</i>
<i>captain of the</i> Jolly Roger.

47:02.682 --> 47:07.278
If you are Hook,
then who am I?

47:07.353 --> 47:10.186
You are a codfish.

47:12.224 --> 47:14.692
<i>[Pan Laughing]</i>

47:14.760 --> 47:19.595
<i>Tell me, Hook,</i>
<i>have you another name?</i>

47:19.665 --> 47:21.097
Aye.

47:23.067 --> 47:26.264
- Vegetable?
- No.

47:26.337 --> 47:28.328
- Mineral?
- No.

47:28.406 --> 47:31.135
<i>Animal?</i>
<i>Yes.</i>

47:31.207 --> 47:34.506
- Man?
- [Own Voice]
No!

47:34.578 --> 47:37.138
- Boy?
- Yes!

47:37.213 --> 47:39.613
- <i>Ordinary boy?</i>
- No!

47:39.683 --> 47:43.174
- Wonderful boy?
- <i>Yes.! Do you give up?</i>

47:43.252 --> 47:45.277
- Yes!
- I am...

47:45.354 --> 47:48.448
- History.
- Peter, look out!

47:48.524 --> 47:51.321
<i>[Laughing]</i>

47:56.431 --> 47:58.661
There he is!

47:58.733 --> 48:01.667
It is your requiem mass, boy.

48:02.803 --> 48:05.067
[Shouting]

48:05.138 --> 48:09.199
Ready to lose the other one?
Not this time.

48:20.286 --> 48:23.152
[Gasps]
[Chuckling]

48:24.222 --> 48:27.851
Ooh-ooh, girlie.
[Chuckles]

48:27.926 --> 48:32.225
[Screams]
<i>Who be you to call me girlie?</i>

48:36.834 --> 48:39.667
- [Peter Laughing]
- Ow.

48:39.737 --> 48:42.603
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Open the gate.!</i>

48:42.672 --> 48:44.333
- [Shouting]
- [Screams]

48:45.475 --> 48:47.409
<i>Teddy.!</i>

48:47.477 --> 48:49.035
[Groans]

48:56.084 --> 48:58.018
Ew.

49:00.155 --> 49:02.384
Oh.

49:14.367 --> 49:16.198
[Grunting]

49:19.039 --> 49:21.530
If I were you, I'd give up.

49:21.608 --> 49:24.701
If you were me, I'd be ugly.

49:33.317 --> 49:36.047
No!

49:36.120 --> 49:38.088
Ready?

49:38.156 --> 49:40.624
Fire!

49:53.436 --> 49:56.269
<i>[John]</i>
<i>Get the boat.!</i>

49:56.338 --> 49:58.829
- [All Shouting]
- [Screaming]

50:06.381 --> 50:08.645
[Coughs]

50:13.754 --> 50:16.951
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

50:19.093 --> 50:21.994
Turn the boat around.

50:22.062 --> 50:23.995
Turn it around!

50:33.305 --> 50:35.830
And now, Peter Pan,

50:36.908 --> 50:39.274
you shall die.

50:45.483 --> 50:49.283
To die will be
an awfully big adventure.

50:53.923 --> 50:55.948
<i>[Ticking]</i>
Oh, no.

51:00.730 --> 51:02.891
[Roars]

51:05.868 --> 51:08.530
- Shoot it!
- [Men Shouting]

51:12.941 --> 51:16.205
[Grunts]

51:16.277 --> 51:19.212
[Children Laughing]

51:20.581 --> 51:22.947
You.

51:23.017 --> 51:24.677
[Gasps]

51:33.593 --> 51:35.355
Smee!

51:37.129 --> 51:40.621
<i>Smee.!</i>

51:40.699 --> 51:42.826
It's all a bit tragic,
really, isn't it?

51:42.902 --> 51:45.893
<i>[Children Whooping]</i>

51:47.405 --> 51:50.272
<i>**[Woman Chanting]</i>
<i>**[Drum Beating]</i>

52:04.654 --> 52:06.679
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>The warrior is wounded.</i>

52:06.756 --> 52:11.557
She is calling forth
the spirit of the eagle
to heal the warrior.

52:11.627 --> 52:13.561
It's so impressive.

52:16.131 --> 52:18.599
The warrior is healed.

52:34.948 --> 52:37.940
- <i>[Man Shouts In</i>
<i>Foreign Language]</i>
- [All Shout]

52:39.285 --> 52:41.014
[Whooping]

52:45.157 --> 52:47.955
Peter?
Shh.

52:52.097 --> 52:54.361
Peter?
[Gasps]

54:59.111 --> 55:01.102
Evil day.

55:09.120 --> 55:11.953
He has found himself a...

55:14.659 --> 55:17.559
[Chattering]

55:17.627 --> 55:19.618
Wendy?

55:20.864 --> 55:24.300
<i>And Hook is all alone.</i>

55:24.368 --> 55:28.064
Me too.
You too?

55:28.137 --> 55:30.799
Banished? Tsk, tsk.
The dog.

55:36.545 --> 55:40.571
[Chatters]
I think you and I...

55:43.852 --> 55:45.979
should talk.

55:52.059 --> 55:53.993
Wendy?

55:54.061 --> 55:57.689
It's only make-believe,
isn't it?

55:59.198 --> 56:02.395
That you and I are...

56:04.237 --> 56:06.899
Oh. Yes.

56:09.741 --> 56:11.606
Wendy?

56:13.745 --> 56:17.441
You see, it would make me seem
so old to be a real father.

56:21.485 --> 56:23.476
Peter,

56:24.755 --> 56:28.747
what are your real feelings?
Feelings?

56:28.825 --> 56:30.952
What do you feel?

56:31.027 --> 56:34.656
Happiness? Sadness?

56:34.731 --> 56:36.926
Jealousy?
Jealousy?

56:37.000 --> 56:39.593
Tink!
Anger?

56:39.668 --> 56:41.693
- Anger.
- [Branch Snaps]

56:45.074 --> 56:47.065
Hook.

56:48.509 --> 56:50.443
Love?

56:53.181 --> 56:55.843
- Love?
- Love.

56:55.917 --> 56:58.384
I have never heard of it.

56:58.452 --> 57:01.683
I think you have, Peter.

57:01.755 --> 57:04.155
I daresay you've
felt it yourself...

57:04.224 --> 57:08.023
for something or... someone.

57:11.831 --> 57:16.200
Never. Even the sound
of it offends me.

57:16.268 --> 57:18.497
Peter.
[Gasps]

57:18.570 --> 57:22.370
<i>Why do you spoil everything?</i>
<i>We have fun, don't we?</i>

57:22.440 --> 57:26.399
I taught you to fight and to fly.
What more could there be?

57:26.478 --> 57:30.675
There is so much more.
What? What else is there?

57:30.747 --> 57:35.241
I don't know.
I think it becomes clearer
when you grow up.

57:35.319 --> 57:38.152
Well, I will not grow up!
You cannot make me!

57:38.222 --> 57:41.088
I will banish you like Tinker Bell!
I will not be banished!

57:41.157 --> 57:43.921
Then go home.
Go home and grow up.

57:43.993 --> 57:47.087
And take your feelings
with you!
Peter!

57:47.163 --> 57:49.494
Peter, come back! Peter!

57:52.567 --> 57:56.059
[Tinker Bell Chattering]

57:56.138 --> 57:58.731
<i>[Wendy Crying]</i>

58:09.849 --> 58:12.317
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Peter did not want Wendy to leave.</i>

58:13.353 --> 58:15.913
<i>Once again,</i>
<i>he visited Wendy's home...</i>

58:15.989 --> 58:19.719
<i>to see if Mr. And Mrs. Darling</i>
<i>had closed the window yet.</i>

58:22.261 --> 58:26.163
<i>But, as before, he saw</i>
<i>Mrs. Darling in her chair...</i>

58:26.231 --> 58:30.291
<i>by the window, her eyes tired</i>
<i>with searching the heavens.</i>

58:31.302 --> 58:33.361
<i>Wendy.</i>

58:34.872 --> 58:37.466
Wendy.

58:37.542 --> 58:39.475
<i>Wendy.</i>

58:43.914 --> 58:46.314
We can't both have her, lady.

58:47.851 --> 58:51.479
<i>[Windowpane Squeaking]</i>

58:59.028 --> 59:01.291
[Gasps]

59:01.362 --> 59:04.854
John! Michael!

59:04.933 --> 59:07.458
Wendy!
[Barks]

59:07.535 --> 59:10.128
[Gasps]
The window's closed.

59:12.105 --> 59:14.835
- George! George, help me!
- <i>What is it? Have they returned?</i>

59:14.908 --> 59:19.368
The window is closed.
It must always be open for them.

59:19.446 --> 59:22.846
- <i>Always. Always.</i>
- [All Grunting]

59:33.491 --> 59:35.652
They've not returned.

01:00:05.754 --> 01:00:08.416
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

01:00:11.792 --> 01:00:14.852
<i>**[Harpsichord]</i>
<i>[Hook]</i>
<i>*Avast belay the English brig *</i>

01:00:14.929 --> 01:00:17.955
<i>* We took and quickly sank *</i>

01:00:18.032 --> 01:00:21.694
<i>*And for a warning</i>
<i>to the crew *</i>

01:00:21.768 --> 01:00:24.896
<i>* We made them walk the plank *</i>

01:00:24.971 --> 01:00:28.498
<i>* Yo ho, yo ho</i>
<i>the frisky plank *</i>

01:00:28.575 --> 01:00:31.805
<i>*He walks along it so *</i>
Welcome. Shh, shh.

01:00:31.877 --> 01:00:36.405
* Till it goes down
and you's go down *

01:00:36.482 --> 01:00:42.442
<i>* To tooral looral loo</i> **
Wrote it himself.

01:00:46.291 --> 01:00:49.556
Wendy, darling.

01:00:53.764 --> 01:00:55.857
Muscat, miss?

01:00:55.932 --> 01:00:58.025
I'm a little girl.

01:00:58.101 --> 01:01:00.035
Rum, then?
[Chuckles]

01:01:00.103 --> 01:01:02.593
No, thank you.

01:01:02.672 --> 01:01:05.664
I'm told you ran away from home.

01:01:05.741 --> 01:01:10.474
L... I had never
thought of it that way.

01:01:10.546 --> 01:01:12.775
<i>[Tinker Bell Chattering]</i>

01:01:12.847 --> 01:01:15.338
<i>I suppose I did.</i>

01:01:15.417 --> 01:01:17.317
How wonderful.

01:01:17.385 --> 01:01:21.787
[Screams]
<i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>My parents wanted me to grow up.</i>

01:01:21.855 --> 01:01:25.689
[Scoffs]
Growing up is such
a barbarous business,

01:01:25.759 --> 01:01:29.286
full of inconvenience
and pimples.

01:01:29.363 --> 01:01:31.830
Things were simpler
when I was younger.

01:01:31.898 --> 01:01:35.425
And then the mess starts,
the feelings come.

01:01:37.303 --> 01:01:40.830
Pan is so lucky
to be untroubled by them.

01:01:45.544 --> 01:01:47.705
Oh, no. He cannot love.

01:01:49.047 --> 01:01:51.447
<i>It's part of the riddle</i>
<i>ofhis being.</i>

01:01:53.084 --> 01:01:55.143
Cigar?

01:02:00.324 --> 01:02:04.316
Oh, there, there.

01:02:04.394 --> 01:02:07.295
Shh, shh, shh.
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

01:02:09.065 --> 01:02:11.590
It doesn't
have to be this way.

01:02:15.437 --> 01:02:19.874
Didst thou ever want to be
a pirate, my hearty?

01:02:21.976 --> 01:02:25.912
I once thought
of calling myself...

01:02:25.980 --> 01:02:29.541
Mm?
Red-Handed Jill.

01:02:29.617 --> 01:02:32.779
Oh, what a marvelous name!

01:02:32.853 --> 01:02:35.151
That's what we'll call you
if you join us.

01:02:35.222 --> 01:02:40.592
But what would my duties be?
I could not be expected to pillage.

01:02:40.660 --> 01:02:45.722
Do you, um, by any chance,
tell stories?

01:02:45.798 --> 01:02:48.596
<i>[Wendy]</i>
<i>And they all lived happily...</i>

01:02:48.667 --> 01:02:52.500
<i>ever... after.</i>

01:02:54.305 --> 01:02:56.205
Bravo!

01:02:56.274 --> 01:02:58.765
<i>Bravissimo.!</i>

01:03:02.080 --> 01:03:06.539
Might I have time
to consider your generous offer?

01:03:06.617 --> 01:03:09.814
Absolutely.
Of course, you must.

01:03:09.887 --> 01:03:13.219
My fellows will return you
whence they found you.

01:03:13.289 --> 01:03:18.693
None of my crew will follow you.
I swear it.

01:03:18.761 --> 01:03:22.390
My new obsession is you,

01:03:22.465 --> 01:03:27.094
not dear Peter Pan
or his whereabouts.

01:03:27.169 --> 01:03:29.501
[All Chuckling]

01:03:29.571 --> 01:03:33.131
What would Mother think
of my becoming a pirate?

01:03:33.207 --> 01:03:35.869
Until we meet again.

01:03:38.379 --> 01:03:40.973
<i>[Owl Hooting]</i>

01:03:43.016 --> 01:03:45.576
<i>[Bird Squawking]</i>

01:03:52.192 --> 01:03:54.921
[Squawking]

01:03:57.896 --> 01:04:01.662
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>What would Mother think</i>
<i>if she became a pirate?</i>

01:04:01.733 --> 01:04:06.226
<i>But the more Wendy</i>
<i>thought ofher mother,</i>
<i>the less she could remember.</i>

01:04:06.304 --> 01:04:08.932
- John.
- I wasn't doing anything!

01:04:09.006 --> 01:04:11.304
- John!
- Yes?

01:04:11.375 --> 01:04:14.104
What is your father's name?

01:04:14.177 --> 01:04:17.146
My father's name? Peter.

01:04:17.214 --> 01:04:19.148
Father!
Yea, Peter!

01:04:19.216 --> 01:04:21.480
Michael, who is your mother?

01:04:21.551 --> 01:04:25.748
- Well, he got the easy one.
- You are my mother, Wendy.

01:04:25.821 --> 01:04:28.449
And isn't she just first-class?

01:04:28.524 --> 01:04:32.722
[Howls]
There's a new pirate
aboard the <i>Jolly Roger.</i>

01:04:32.795 --> 01:04:36.662
The mermaids say she
is called Red-Handed Jill.

01:04:36.731 --> 01:04:39.256
Another adventure, boys.
Come on!
[Cheering]

01:04:39.334 --> 01:04:42.770
Red-Handed Jill?
She sounds quite fearsome!

01:04:42.837 --> 01:04:45.805
<i>Fearsome?</i>
<i>She's just a storyteller.</i>

01:04:45.873 --> 01:04:47.966
Just a storyteller?

01:04:49.676 --> 01:04:52.668
Red-Handed Jill
may be a brave swordsman.

01:04:52.746 --> 01:04:55.475
[All Laughing]
A girl like her?

01:04:55.548 --> 01:04:59.314
Brave or not,
I shall run her through!

01:04:59.385 --> 01:05:02.115
<i>[All Cheering]</i>

01:05:02.188 --> 01:05:04.553
<i>[Cheering Stops]</i>

01:05:04.623 --> 01:05:07.251
Then ready yourself, Peter Pan,

01:05:07.325 --> 01:05:10.055
for I am Red-Handed Jill.

01:05:10.128 --> 01:05:12.062
Mother!
Wendy?

01:05:12.130 --> 01:05:14.097
'Tis true, John.

01:05:14.164 --> 01:05:17.998
Your sister has been
invited to piracy.

01:05:21.038 --> 01:05:23.666
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>But, Mother, Hook is a fiend.</i>

01:05:23.741 --> 01:05:27.039
- And a bounder.
- On the contrary,

01:05:27.110 --> 01:05:30.876
I find Captain Hook
to be a man of feeling.

01:05:32.248 --> 01:05:34.511
[Gasps, Whimpers]

01:05:34.583 --> 01:05:38.075
[All Gasp]
Mother and Father
are fighting again.

01:05:38.153 --> 01:05:42.487
Sir, you are both
ungallant and deficient.

01:05:42.558 --> 01:05:44.650
How am I deficient?

01:05:45.826 --> 01:05:47.817
You're just a boy.

01:05:51.999 --> 01:05:54.865
Are you really to be a pirate, Mother?

01:05:54.935 --> 01:05:56.698
No.

01:05:58.505 --> 01:06:00.564
We are going home.

01:06:00.640 --> 01:06:02.335
<i>[All Gasp]</i>
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Home?</i>

01:06:02.409 --> 01:06:05.400
- Leave Neverland?
- <i>[Murmuring]</i>

01:06:08.347 --> 01:06:11.248
We must.

01:06:11.317 --> 01:06:13.581
We have forgotten
our parents.

01:06:13.652 --> 01:06:17.451
<i>We must leave at once</i>
<i>before we...</i>

01:06:17.522 --> 01:06:19.615
in turn are forgotten.

01:06:24.529 --> 01:06:28.931
I've forgotten... my parents.

01:06:28.999 --> 01:06:31.559
<i>We must leave.</i>

01:06:31.635 --> 01:06:33.796
[All Shouting]

01:06:33.870 --> 01:06:35.962
If you wish it.

01:06:36.038 --> 01:06:39.974
- "If you wish it"?
- If you wish it!

01:06:41.877 --> 01:06:44.573
[Parrot Squawking]

01:06:50.051 --> 01:06:52.246
[Squawking]

01:06:54.856 --> 01:06:56.880
[Snickering]

01:06:58.325 --> 01:07:02.056
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill! Kill!

01:07:06.032 --> 01:07:10.901
Don't fret, my dear.
With Pan dead,

01:07:10.970 --> 01:07:14.167
we'll both be free.

01:07:14.240 --> 01:07:16.673
[Chattering]

01:07:16.742 --> 01:07:19.677
I have arranged a fairy guide
to lead you back.

01:07:19.745 --> 01:07:21.679
Peter,

01:07:23.382 --> 01:07:25.781
we've been talking.

01:07:27.318 --> 01:07:29.411
What if you
came back with us?

01:07:29.487 --> 01:07:31.421
<i>Can we go, Peter?</i>

01:07:31.489 --> 01:07:33.855
<i>Please, Peter, can we go?</i>
If you wish it.

01:07:33.924 --> 01:07:35.857
Get your things.

01:07:35.925 --> 01:07:38.189
[All Cheering]

01:07:43.133 --> 01:07:45.601
You too, Peter.

01:07:45.669 --> 01:07:48.831
Would they send me to school?

01:07:53.008 --> 01:07:56.534
Yes.
Then... to an office?

01:07:56.611 --> 01:07:58.772
I suppose so.

01:08:00.415 --> 01:08:02.474
Soon I should be a man.

01:08:05.186 --> 01:08:08.313
- You can't catch me
and make me a man.
- Peter.

01:08:12.359 --> 01:08:17.557
I want always
to be a boy and have fun.

01:08:17.630 --> 01:08:21.999
You say so, but I think
it is your biggest pretend.

01:08:27.072 --> 01:08:30.041
<i>[Tapping]</i>

01:08:31.943 --> 01:08:34.969
[Parrot Squawking]

01:08:35.046 --> 01:08:37.569
[Chattering]

01:08:37.648 --> 01:08:40.310
[Squawks, Gasps]

01:08:42.453 --> 01:08:47.048
[Squawking Continues]

01:08:47.122 --> 01:08:51.082
Oh! Ooh. Ooh-la-la!

01:08:51.160 --> 01:08:54.129
[Chattering]

01:08:56.432 --> 01:08:58.865
[Growling]

01:09:05.607 --> 01:09:08.073
Bye-bye!

